Unlock the Secrets to a Pain-Free Back: The 5 Reasons Why Your Back is Hurting and How to Fix Them Meta Description: Are you tired of dealing with a sore and painful back? Discover the 5 common causes of back pain and how to address them with the Pujats Method. Sign up today at www.pujats.org. Introduction: Back pain is one of the most common complaints among adults. It can be caused by a variety of factors ranging from poor posture to a sedentary lifestyle. The good news is that there are several effective solutions that can help alleviate the pain and prevent it from returning. In this article we will explore the five most common reasons why your back is hurting and how you can use the Pujats Method to get relief. 1. Muscle or Ligament Strain from Repeated Heavy Lifting or Sudden Awkward Movement Heavy lifting and sudden awkward movements can put a lot of stress on the muscles and ligaments in your back. This can result in strain and pain that can last for days or even weeks. If you are dealing with back pain as a result of heavy lifting it is important to take steps to prevent it from happening again. The Pujats Method is an effective solution that can help you build strength and stability in your back muscles reducing the risk of future injuries. 2. Bulging or Herniated Discs Bulging or herniated discs are a common cause of back pain. These conditions occur when the soft spongy material between the vertebrae in your spine begins to bulge or herniate out of place. This can cause pressure on the nerves in your spine leading to pain and discomfort. The Pujats Method can help to release the pressure on your discs providing relief from pain and discomfort. 3. Arthritis or Osteoarthritis Arthritis and osteoarthritis are conditions that can cause pain and inflammation in the joints including the joints in your back. These conditions can make it difficult to move and perform everyday activities leading to pain and discomfort. The Pujats Method is an effective solution for managing arthritis and osteoarthritis in the back providing relief from pain and improving joint mobility. 4. Osteoporosis Osteoporosis causes the bones in your body to become brittle and weak
